glosses.gloss: Nocturnal burrowing mammal of the grasslands of Africa that feeds on termites; sole extant representative of the order Tubulidentata
The aardvark is a medium-sized, burrowing, nocturnal mammal native to Africa.
A burrowing mammal (Orycteropus afer) of southern Africa, having a stocky, hairy body, large ears, a long tubular snout, and powerful digging claws.
The nocturnal, insectivorous, burrowing, mammal Orycteropus afer, of the order Tubulidentata, somewhat resembling a pig, common in some parts of sub-Saharan Africa.
땅돼지는 관치목 땅돼지과의 유일종인 야행성 포유동물으로, 흙돼지, 아드바크라고도 일컫는다.

examples.example: The aardvark burrows in the ground and feeds mostly on termites, which it catches with its long, slimy tongue.

glosses.gloss: The General Dynamics F-111 Aardvark was a supersonic, medium-range interdictor and tactical attack aircraft that also filled the roles of strategic nuclear bomber, aerial reconnaissance, and electronic-warfare aircraft in its various versions.
제너럴 다이내믹스 F-111 아드바크는 중거리 지상 공격기로 사용되었던 군용기이다.
